  "prompt": "Why does stars are not showing in my clash of clans map when I win on fighting with the other random players ?",
  "response": "In Clash of Clans, if you win a battle against another player but do not see stars or trophies awarded, there could be several reasons for this:\n\n1. **No Trophies at Stake**: You may be attacking a base that is not within a trophy range where you can gain trophies. For example, if you are attacking someone too far below or above your trophy count, you might not earn any trophies.\n\n2. **Friendly Challenge**: If the attack was part of a friendly challenge you initiated with a friend, it does not affect trophies or stars since it's meant for practice.\n\n3. **Clan Wars**: If the battle was during a Clan War, you can earn stars for your clan's total score, but these don't translate into trophies. Make sure you are aware of whether the match was a regular raid or a clan war attack.\n\n4. **Attacking Your Own Base**: If you attacked your own base using a second account or during a test setup, you will not earn trophies or stars from that attack.\n\n5. **Technical Issues**: Occasionally, bugs or glitches can prevent the proper updating of your trophy count. Restarting the game or checking for updates may resolve this.\n\n6. **Not Winning**: In Clash of Clans, you'll only earn trophies for winning and destroying a specified percentage of your opponent's village or their Town Hall. If you don\u2019t reach the required percentage or destroy the Town Hall, you may not be awarded stars/trophies.\n\nIf you continue facing issues, it's a good idea to check the game's support forums or contact Supercell support for assistance.",
